<Text>Three years ago, I injured my back & haven't felt right since. During that time, I worked with 5 different chiropractic offices that each told me that they understood why I was in pain & that they were capable of helping me heal. With each chiropractor I worked with, I felt so excited to hear that addressing my pain was a reality, & that they could help me get back to feeling normal. Unfortunately, each time I was told that, I continued to feel pain & discomfort. I was at the end of my rope, didn't even believe chiropractors could help me any longer, & was emotionally in the dumps due to my constant discomfort.

Then, about 4 months ago, I met Dr. Chase. After discussing my situation with him, he convinced me to give chiropractic care one more chance - I was apprehensive at first but figured, what the heck - let's give it one more try.

After 4 months of treatments, this week was the first full week in 3 years that my discomfort hasn't kept me up at night or affected me throughout my entire day & I believe it's due to the quality care I received at Life Source Chiropractic. Beyond their high level of care, their support staff has been impeccably professional, positive, & helpful. Take it from someone that knows local chiropractors - don't waste your time & energy going elsewhere. Stop reading reviews now & just go ahead & schedule your appointment. <Text>Went for the first time since the last day they were open due to the pandemic. They opened on 04/11/21, and safety precautions are taken seriously. Great food at a very low price. Fresh variety of sushi, which is made in public view. A huge variety of food, seafood, desserts and fruit. The customer service is great. When a patron is finished with a plate, the staff clears it off the table promptly. The staff will refill drinks constantly as well. The staff is very friendly. I bring my mom for lunch every Monday or Tuesday. I recommend this place to all my friends and family. Food is always fresh and piping hot.</review>

<gmapID>0x80c2d62df724d2fb:0xf2b752f15b27f97< /gmapID><Response>None< /Response>< Review>
Huge variety. All the food was good & fresh, no complaints in that department. Nice ambiance (around the Christmas season they even have a holiday tree!). Lots of good dessert options: several kinds of pudding, jello, fresh fruit, cookies, etc.

They understandably keep a close eye on people hovering around the food area, but most of the workers were very polite. Lots of parking though the lot does get crowded. Prices are similar to what most buffets around here charge - very reasonably priced, like $10 to $12 depending on what day/time you go. Good sized place with decent amount of space if you want to bring a group.</Review>

< Text>
First off the front desk lady is very nice but hard to understand unless you speak Asian. They make you leave a deposit for the tv remote and wi-fi which is weird. The wifi wouldn't even connect on any of our phones (there were three of us), so that ended up being a waste of time.

I asked for a non-smoking room when I called in and they said no problem, only to find out the room wreaked with a variety of different smells including cigarette.

Third, the bathroom looks like it's taken from a broken down apartment in New York City. Carvings on the mirrors and counter tops, little to no toilet paper, shower towels were folded like they were clean, but they were dirty. There were toiletry items left in the bathroom from the precious guest.

Beds- this is the main thing used when staying in a hotel...THAT IS the reason most people get them and especially in this area. TERRIBLE. Dirty top cover, hair on the pillows, all kinds of grime on the sheets which also smelled horrible.

I highly suggest finding another place to stay. I would have rather slept in my vehicle.< /Text>

< text>
Price is great, dental care is great. Nice waiting room with toys. My 3 yr old had a fun experience, her first visit to a dentist. The staff was very sweet with my 1 yr old, too. But the environment was unpleasant for me. I'm very sensitive, but many kids are too, so I feel like people need to know about this. The top things I didn't like is there were TVs in the waiting area and the exam room constantly on, and the dentist Dr. Rex didn't make eye contact with me even when he was talking to me, even though he seemed friendly enough. Also Dr. Rex asked my kid some questions while she was watching the TV, instead of turning it off for a minute to have her full attention! I know that's normal for some people, but it's not the best approach if you want the kid to see you as a trusted authority. Plus they didn't try to teach her about dental health at all. I was expecting they would. Isn't that what dentists all used to do? The TVs, plus people talking, plus lots of prizes, plus me needing to wrangle my 1 yr old of course, made it overwhelming for me and I was so glad to leave. They did help my 3 yr old be comfortable! She is extroverted. I just wish it was less of an...intense experience. I'd prefer the good old fashioned type of professional demeanor, not this modern total sensory stimulation they seem to think kids need to be able to enjoy themselves. Next time, I'll ask to have the TVs off more, and see if things go better for us.<//text>

< Text>
Very good experience, highly recommend!!

- before I went, I checked the reviews and find out the main problem is deal with payment. So I well prepared before I went. I called on last Wed and got an appointment Friday(yesterday). I received my approval letter from my insurance company and brought it with me. Receptionist don't need it and just asked for my ID and ins card.
- Receptionist are very nice and helpful :
The receptionist(forgot to ask her name) was nice and explained to me when I had questions from the forms, when I finished the first page, she took it and process first so I was called not even I finished completing all forms.
I want to get a copy of my MRI and I forgot to mention yesterday when I left so I went back this morning and I was lucky that they are open. Although their office shows closed on Saturday but they open for patients with appointment. Receptionist Cindy was very nice to burn the CD right away for me.
- Technican Mike was very nice and gentle. He    answered any questions that I asked. Now I know the difference between a normal MRI and an open MRI. If people don't feel comfortable to get into a closed MRI, they can choose the open one but it will be at least double the time. My coworker told me that  his whole MRI appointment took nearly 1-1/2 to 2hrs but it only took me 40mins. 1.5T might be 10-15 mins longer than 3T machine depend on what part of the body so 3T is the fastest, heehee...
- very convenience to change to another location. This company is a group, I make a simple call and changed my appointment from San Francisco to Daly City and I don't need to give my insurance info again.
- feel comfortable, although they don't have music to listen but with double ear plugs, put into my ears and add a headset ear plug outside, it cuts down a lot of noise. Of course you can still hear it, but I just treated it as different types of music rymthum. With the blanklet totally cover me, it makes me feel very comfortable and relax, so time go fast.
- very easy parking, they are located at the same building of AAA with a huge free parking lot.

Thanks SimonMed Imaging/Daly City!<//Text>
